.TH "nvram_create_partition" 9 "nvram_create_partition" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nvram_create_partition \- Create a partition in nvram
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "loff_t" nvram_create_partition
.BI "(const char *name "  ","
.BI "int sig "  ","
.BI "int req_size "  ","
.BI "int min_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
name of the partition to create
.IP "sig" 12
signature of the partition to create
.IP "req_size" 12
size of data to allocate in bytes
.IP "min_size" 12
minimum acceptable size (0 means req_size)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns a negative error code or a positive nvram index
of the beginning of the data area of the newly created
partition. If you provided a min_size smaller than req_size
you need to query for the actual size yourself after the
call using \fBnvram_partition_get_size\fP.
